"Run the <command>make help_params</command> command in the root directory of "
"a book for a full list of parameters that can be set in the "
"<filename>Makefile</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: Using_Publican.xml:205
#, no-c-format
msgid "Book_Info.xml"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:206
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename>Book_Info.xml</filename> file is used to set the book ID, "
"title, subtitle, issue and product numbers, and an abstract which appears at "
"the start of the book. The following is an example <filename>Book_Info.xml</"
"filename> file for the Test_Book book, with instructions following "
"afterwards:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: Using_Publican.xml:209
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<xi:include href=\"extras/Book_Info.xmlt\" parse=\"text\" xmlns:xi=\"http://"
"www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></xi:include>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: Using_Publican.xml:212
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;bookinfo id=\"<replaceable>book_id</replaceable>\"&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:214
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Book ID is used internally and is not displayed to end users when the "
"book is built. replace <replaceable>book_id</replaceable> with an ID for the "
"book; however, if you run the <command>make clean_ids</command> command, "
"this ID along with all other IDs will be changed to a <replaceable>Book_Name-"
"Title</replaceable> format, where \"Title\" is the title of the article, "
"book, section, or chapter."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: Using_Publican.xml:220
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;title&gt;<replaceable>title</replaceable>&lt;/title&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:222
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The title of the book, for example: &quot;Server Configuration Guide&quot;. "
"The title appears under the product name when the book is built. Replace "
"<replaceable>title</replaceable> with the title of the book. A title is "
"required to build an RPM. When building a book as an RPM the title is used "
"as the part of the RPM name in the RPM spec file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: Using_Publican.xml:226 Using_Publican.xml:248 Using_Publican.xml:265
#: Using_Publican.xml:282 Using_Publican.xml:296 Using_Publican.xml:420
#, no-c-format
msgid "Important"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:227 Using_Publican.xml:249
#, no-c-format
msgid "This field can only contain the values: 'a-z', 'A-Z' and '_'."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: Using_Publican.xml:234
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;subtitle&gt;<replaceable>subtitle</replaceable>&lt;/subtitle&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:236
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The subtitle is ... The subtitle appears under the title when the book is "
"built. Replace <replaceable>subtitle</replaceable> with a subtitle for the "
"book. A subtitle is required to build an RPM. When building a book as an RPM "
"the subtitle is used as the <computeroutput>Summary</computeroutput> in the "
"RPM spec file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: Using_Publican.xml:242
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;productname&gt;<replaceable>productname</replaceable>&lt;/productname&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:244
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The name of the product or product stream, for example: &quot;Red Hat "
"Enterprise Linux&quot; or &quot;JBoss Enterprise Application Platform&quot;. "
"Replace <replaceable>productname</replaceable> with the product name of the "
"book. When building a book as an RPM the productname is used as the part of "
"the RPM name in the RPM spec file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: Using_Publican.xml:256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;productnumber&gt;<replaceable>productnumber</replaceable>&lt;/"
"productnumber&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:258
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The version number of the product to which the book applies, for example "
"&quot;5.1&quot; for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 5.1, 4.3 for JBoss EAP 4.3. If "
"your book does not apply to a product then you can put whatever you like. "
"Replace <replaceable>productnumber</replaceable> with the product number."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:261
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Running the <command>create_book --name <replaceable> Book_Name</"
"replaceable> --version <replaceable>version</replaceable></command> command "
"correctly configures the product number."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:266 Using_Publican.xml:283
#, no-c-format
msgid "This field can only contain the values: '0-9' and '.'."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: Using_Publican.xml:273
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;edition&gt;<replaceable>edition</replaceable>&lt;/edition&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:275
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the edition number of the book. The first edition of the book should "
"be 1.0 (you may like to use 0.y for alpha and beta releases). Subsequent "
"edition should increment the 1.y to indicate to readers that the book is a "
"new edition. Replace <replaceable>edition</replaceable> with the x.y edition "
"number. The edition changes the version number (the first two digits) when "
"building a book with the <command>tar</command> or <command>srpm</command> "
"options. For example, setting the edition to <filename>1.2</filename> and "
"building the book using the <command>make srpm-en-US</command> command, "
"would create an RPM file named <filename><replaceable>productname</"
"replaceable>-<replaceable>title</replaceable>-<replaceable>productnumber</"
"replaceable>-en-US-1.2-0.src.rpm</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:278
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Running the <command>create_book --name<replaceable> Book_Name</replaceable> "
"--edition <replaceable>x</replaceable>.<replaceable>y</replaceable></"
"command> command correctly configures the edition."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: Using_Publican.xml:290
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;pubsnumber&gt;<replaceable>pubsnumber</replaceable>&lt;/pubsnumber&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:292
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The pubsnumber changes the release number (the last digit) when building a "
"book with the <filename>tar</filename> or <filename>srpm</filename> options. "
"For example, setting the pubsnumber to <filename>1</filename> and building "
"the book using the <command>make srpm-en-US</command> command, would create "
"an RPM file named <filename><replaceable>productname</replaceable>-"
"<replaceable>title</replaceable>-<replaceable>productnumber</replaceable>-en-"
"US-<replaceable>edition</replaceable>-1.src.rpm</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:297
#, no-c-format
msgid "This field can only contain the values: '0-9'."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: Using_Publican.xml:304
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;abstract&gt;&lt;para&gt;<replaceable>abstract</replaceable>&lt;/para&gt;"
"&lt;/abstract&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:306
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A brief description of the subject of a book that appears before the main "
"body of text in html and pdf output. This paragraph indicates to the reader "
"in a general sense what the book covers, and allows them to evaluate whether "
"or not they need or want to read it, without having to scan the entire book. "
"It is also used in the rpm description, which allows people installing "
"packages to do the same thing before installing a documentation package. "
"Replace <replaceable>abstract</replaceable> with the abstract for the book. "
"The abstract appears before the table of contents when using HTML, and on "
"the second page when using PDF. When building a book as an RPM the abstract "
"is used as the <computeroutput>description</computeroutput> in the RPM spec "
"file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: Using_Publican.xml:312
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;year&gt;&amp;YEAR&semi;&lt;/year&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:314
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename>&amp;YEAR&semi;</filename> entity is defined in "
"<filename><replaceable>Book_Name</replaceable>.ent</filename>. Use this to "
"set the copyright year of the book. Refer to <xref linkend=\"sect-Publican-"
"Files_in_the_Book_directory-Book_Name.ent\"/> for configuration details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: Using_Publican.xml:320
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;holder&gt;&amp;HOLDER&semi;&lt;/holder&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:322
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename>&amp;HOLDER&semi;</filename> entity is defined in "
"<filename><replaceable>Book_Name</replaceable>.ent</filename>. Use this to "
"set the copyright holder of the book. Refer to <xref linkend=\"sect-Publican-"
"Files_in_the_Book_directory-Book_Name.ent\"/> for configuration details. The "
"copyright section is not required."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:331
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This idiosyncratic information organisation (ie, the use above of &lt;"
"title&gt;, &lt;subtitle&gt; and &lt;issuenum&gt;) is a legacy of the old and "
"now entirely deprecated SGML system once used internally at Red Hat. If we "
"had our time again, for example, we'd use &lt;productname&gt; and &lt;"
"productnumber&gt; for the Product Name and Product Version Number, instead "
"of &lt;title&gt; and &lt;issuenum&gt;. 250 books later, however, changing "
"not just the tags but the templates and associated CSS and XSL is more work "
"than it is worth."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: Using_Publican.xml:338
#, no-c-format
msgid "Author_Group.xml"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:339
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the <filename>Author_Group.xml</filename> file to configure author "
"details. This file is not required. The following is an example "
"<filename>Author_Group.xml</filename> file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: Using_Publican.xml:342
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<xi:include href=\"extras/Author_Group.xmlt\" parse=\"text\" xmlns:xi="
"\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></xi:include>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:343
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename>Author_Group.xml</filename> file does not have to contain all "
"of the above information: include as much or as little as required."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:346
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Delete the following line from Book_Info.xml to prevent author information "
"being included in the built versions of a book:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: Using_Publican.xml:349
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;xi:include href=\"Author_Group.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/"
"XInclude\" /&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: Using_Publican.xml:353
#, no-c-format
msgid "Chapter.xml"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename>Chapter.xml</filename> file is a template for creating chapter "
"files. Chapter files contain the content that make up a book. The following "
"is a chapter template (<filename>Chapter.xml</filename>) that is created "
"after running the <command>create_book</command> command. Note the "
"<filename>DOCTYPE</filename> is set to <filename>chapter</filename>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: Using_Publican.xml:357
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<xi:include href=\"extras/Chapter.xmlt\" parse=\"text\" xmlns:xi=\"http://"
"www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></xi:include>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:358
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter has two sections, <filename>Section 1 Test</filename> and "
"<filename>Section 2 Test</filename>. Please refer to <ulink url=\"http://"
"docbook.org/tdg/en/html/chapter.html\"></ulink> for further information "
"about chapters."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:363
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The chapter file should be renamed to reflect the chapter subject. For "
"example, a chapter on product installation could be named "
"<filename>Installation.xml</filename>, whereas a chapter on setting up a "
"piece of software would be better called <filename>Setup.xml</filename> or "
"<filename>Configuration.xml</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: Using_Publican.xml:370
#, no-c-format
msgid "Book_Name.xml"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:371
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename><replaceable>Book_Name</replaceable>.xml</filename> file "
"contains <filename>xi:include</filename> directives to include the chapters "
"for a book. Chapters are contained in separate XML files, and the "
"<filename><replaceable>Book_Name</replaceable>.xml</filename> file brings "
"them together into a single book."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:374
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following is an example <filename><replaceable>Book_Name</replaceable>."
"xml</filename> file. Note the <filename>DOCTYPE</filename> is set to "
"<filename>book</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: Using_Publican.xml:377
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<xi:include href=\"extras/Book_Name.xmlt\" parse=\"text\" xmlns:xi=\"http://"
"www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></xi:include>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:378
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This example loads the <computeroutput>Book_Info.xml</computeroutput>, "
"<computeroutput>Preface.xml</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>Chapter.xml</"
"computeroutput>, and <computeroutput>Appendix.xml</computeroutput> XML files."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:383
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The order in which chapters are listed matters. When this example book is "
"built, Book_Info.xml will precede Preface.xml which will precede Chapter."
"xml, and so on."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:387
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename><replaceable>Book_Name</replaceable>.xml</filename> file is "
"not limited to using <filename>xi:include</filename> directives. Books can "
"be created using a single XML file. The following is an example of a book "
"created using a single XML file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: Using_Publican.xml:390
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;book&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;chapter&gt;\n"
"&lt;title&gt;Chapter 1&lt;/title&gt;\n"
"        &lt;para&gt;\n"
"                A paragraph in Chapter 1.\n"
"        &lt;/para&gt;\n"
"        &lt;section id=\"section1\"&gt;\n"
"        &lt;title&gt;Chapter 1 Section 1&lt;/title&gt;\n"
"                &lt;para&gt;\n"
"                        A paragraph in Section 1.\n"
"                &lt;/para&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/section&gt;\n"
"        &lt;section id=\"section2\"&gt;\n"
"        &lt;title&gt;Chapter 1 Section 2&lt;/title&gt;\n"
"                &lt;para&gt;\n"
"                        A paragraph in Section 2.\n"
"                &lt;/para&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/section&gt;\n"
"&lt;/chapter&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;chapter&gt;\n"
"&lt;title&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/title&gt;\n"
"        &lt;para&gt;\n"
"                A paragraph in Chapter 2.\n"
"        &lt;/para&gt;\n"
"&lt;/chapter&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;/book&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:391
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This book contains two chapters. Chapter one contains two sections. Please "
"refer to <ulink url=\"http://docbook.org/tdg/en/html/section.html\"></ulink> "
"for further information about sections, and <ulink url=\"http://docbook.org/"
"tdg/en/html/book.html\"></ulink> for further information about books."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: Using_Publican.xml:397
#, no-c-format
msgid "Book_Name.ent"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:398
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename><replaceable>Book_Name</replaceable>.ent</filename> file is "
"used to define local entities. You must define <computeroutput>YEAR</"
"computeroutput> and <computeroutput>HOLDER</computeroutput> entities, "
"otherwise the book will not build:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: Using_Publican.xml:402
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<xi:include href=\"extras/Book_Name.ent\" parse=\"text\" xmlns:xi=\"http://"
"www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></xi:include>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:404
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <computeroutput>YEAR</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>HOLDER</"
"computeroutput> entities are used for copyright information. Use entities to "
"make writing commonly used terms quicker:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: Using_Publican.xml:408
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;!ENTITY FDP \"Fedora Documentation Project\"&gt;\n"
"&lt;!ENTITY FDS \"Fedora Directory Server\"&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:410
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Two entities are defined: <computeroutput>FDP</computeroutput> and "
"<computeroutput>FDS</computeroutput>. Instead of typing "
"<computeroutput>Fedora Documentation Project</computeroutput> you can use "
"<computeroutput>&amp;FDP&semi;</computeroutput>. The build system adds the "
"required entities to the XML files at build time. In the example above, "
"<computeroutput>&amp;FDP&semi;</computeroutput> would be replaced with "
"Fedora Documentation Project."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: Using_Publican.xml:415
#, no-c-format
msgid "Revision_History.xml"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: Using_Publican.xml:416
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make will search for the first XML file in the $(XML_LANG) directory "
"containing a revhistory tag. Publican will use that file to build the RPM "
"revision history from."
msgstr ""

